    • Method Detail

      • getObstacleCount

        public static int getObstacleCount()

      • randomizeEste

        public void randomizeEste()
        This method is used to randomize what obstacle to show next. first we randomize a number in a do/while to make sure that we randomize it at least once. While loop condition is that the obstacle hasn't been seen yet. (See: checkAndSetSeen()) If the obstacle is new, load the obstacle through the BundleHandler. And set booleans.

      • setBooleans

        public void setBooleans(boolean transition,
                        boolean result)
        This method is used to set booleans for what part to load of the .atlas next. (When transition is true, load the part that is shown when in transition screen and when result is true, load the part that is shown after the drawing mechanic) This could've been done in a single boolean, but I think this is more easy to understand.
        Parameters:
        transition - If this is true, load the part that is used in the transition screens
        result - If this is true, load the part that is used in the in the result screens.

      • setTexture

        private void setTexture()
        This method is used to set the texture that we want to render next. Which part to load, depends on the setBooleans(boolean, boolean) method.

      • checkAndSetSeen

        private boolean checkAndSetSeen()
        This method is used to check whether we have seen the current obstacle during this playthrough already. This is done using an a boolean array where we change the boolean to true if we haven't seen it yet. Obviously if the boolean is already true, we return false This is used as a helper class for the randomizeEste() method.
        Returns:
        Whether we have seen the current obstacle already this playthrough.

      • initseenAlready

        public void initseenAlready()
        This method is used to reset the boolean (All of them to false) array when starting a new playthrough.
